\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_gsl$fit_bspp_per95[which(bspp_df2_ts_gsl$spp_name %in% "Tilia americana")]}]))
, including \Ball: $\beta = $
\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_gsl$fit_bspp[which(bspp_df2_ts_gsl$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]}, $UI_{90}$[\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_gsl$fit_bspp_per5[which(bspp_df2_ts_gsl$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]},
\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_gsl$fit_bspp_per95[which(bspp_df2_ts_gsl$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]}] (Figure \ref{fig:wcmuplotbsppTS} b) and f)). These estimates were also unchanged when using budburst instead of leafout as  the start of the growing season (Figure \ref{fig:buburstVSleafoutTS}b) (Table \ref{tab:ts_slope_table}).

% SOS
\item Growth did not change in response to the start of season for any species
(\Arub: $\beta = $ \Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_sos$fit_bspp[which(bspp_df2_ts_sos$spp_name %in% "Acer rubrum")]}, $UI_{90}$[\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_sos$fit_bspp_per5[which(bspp_df2_ts_sos$spp_name %in% "Acer rubrum")]}, \Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_sos$fit_bspp_per95[which(bspp_df2_ts_sos$spp_name %in% "Acer rubrum")]}],
